The paper deals with video object removal using deep learning-based methods, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of optical flow warping and image-based inpainting also suggests that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel learning-based approach, which may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
